        "subtitle": "Premium Japanese Steel Performance",
        "intro_content": "<p><strong>VG10 knives</strong> represent one of the most respected steel grades in Japanese knife making, prized for the ideal balance of hardness, edge retention, and corrosion resistance. XinZuo knives use 10Cr15CoMoV steel, which is the Chinese equivalent of VG10, delivering the same cutting performance at a more accessible price point. Every blade is forged in Yangjiang, hardened to 60+ HRC, and ground to a 15-degree edge angle for surgical sharpness that VG10 steel is famous for. The 10Cr15CoMoV core is wrapped in 67 layers of Damascus steel in our premium lines, combining VG10-class performance with stunning visual patterns that make each blade unique. If you have been searching for <strong>VG10 kitchen knives</strong> that deliver genuine Japanese steel performance without the Japanese price tag, XinZuo is the answer. Our collection includes chef knives, santoku, nakiri, and complete knife sets, all built on this proven VG10-equivalent steel that professional and home cooks trust worldwide.</p>",
